text: Archibald Cameron may refer to: *Archibald Cameron of Lochiel (1707–1753), Jacobite leader *Archibald Donald Cameron (1866–1946), minister of the Free Church of Scotland *Sir Archibald Cameron (British Army officer) (1870–1944), British general *Archibald Cameron (sailor) (1919–1987), Canadian Olympian ==See also== *Archie Cameron (1895–1956), Australian politician *
title: Archibald Cameron
